-- Regression for GH #260: a DOCTEST-bearing module whose type error lives in a
-- function NO doctest exercises.  `medaka test` used to green-light it (the
-- doctest driver elaborates but never surfaces the accumulated type errors) while
-- `medaka check` rejected it — test-green / check-dies, the repo's #1 bug class
-- inverted.  `medaka test` now type-checks the module the way `check` does and
-- fails the whole run BEFORE running any example.  The golden is the located
-- type error, not "1/1 passed".
bad : Int -> String
bad x = x + 1

good : Int -> Int
good x = x * 2

-- > good 5
-- 10
